{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Information about an installed application and methods to launch"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it (with file arguments)."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AppInfo"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"GAppInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppLaunchContext"},{"text":" are used for describing and launching","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"applications installed on the system.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As of GLib 2.20, URIs will always be converted to POSIX paths","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.File.get_path"},{"type":"text","text":"]) when using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AppInfo.launch"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"even if the application requested an URI and not a POSIX path. For example"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for a desktop-file based application with the following Exec key:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["Exec=totem `U`"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"and a single URI, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sftp:\/\/foo\/file.avi"},{"type":"text","text":", then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"\/home\/user\/.gvfs\/sftp on foo\/file.avi","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be passed. This will only work","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if a set of suitable GIO extensions (such as GVfs 2.26 compiled with FUSE","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"support), is available and operational; if this is not the case, the URI","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be passed unmodified to the application. Some URIs, such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mailto:"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of course cannot be mapped to a POSIX path (in GVfs there’s no FUSE mount"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for it); such URIs will be passed unmodified to the application.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifically for GVfs 2.26 and later, the POSIX URI will be mapped"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"back to the GIO URI in the [iface","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/File","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] constructors (since GVfs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implements the GVfs extension point). As such, if the application"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"needs to examine the URI, it needs to use [method"},{"code":"Gio.File.get_uri","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or similar on [iface"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/File","type":"reference"},{"text":"]. In other words, an application cannot","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"assume that the URI passed to e.g. [func"},{"code":"Gio.File.new_for_commandline_arg","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is equal to the result of [method"},{"code":"Gio.File.get_uri","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]. The following snippet","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"illustrates this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["GFile *f;","char *uri;","","file = g_file_new_for_commandline_arg (uri_from_commandline);","","uri = g_file_get_uri (file);","strcmp (uri, uri_from_commandline) == 0;","g_free (uri);","","if (g_file_has_uri_scheme (file, \"cdda\"))","  {","    \/\/ do something special with uri","  }","g_object_unref (file);"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This code will work when both "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cdda:\/\/sr0\/Track 1.wav"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/home\/user\/.gvfs\/cdda on sr0\/Track 1.wav"},{"type":"text","text":" is passed to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"application. It should be noted that it’s generally not safe"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for applications to rely on the format of a particular URIs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Different launcher applications (e.g. file managers) may have"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"different ideas of what a given URI means.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GAppInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"code":"GAppInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoRef"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/appinfo"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"AppInfo","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"title":"AppInfo","externalID":"s:3GIO7AppInfoC","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AppInfo","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(_:)-2qvcl","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(_:)-3k2b4","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(_:)-5b4jc","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(_:)-70u65","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(_:)-871xy","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(raw:)-3cs90","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(raw:)-5bp7j","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(retainingRaw:)-ltq7","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/init(retainingRaw:)-x0qu"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfo\/m